<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n42002e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n42" href="#n42002e">N42 (VI.B.31)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n42all.htm#n42002e"> 2(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> sacrilegious / confession</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Not hundreds, but thousands of times, I have heard from the lips of dying girls, as well as of married women, the awful words: &ldquo;I am for ever lost! All my past confessions and communions have been so many sacrileges! I have never dared to answer correctly the questions of my confessors! Shame has sealed my lips and damned my soul!&rdquo; <small> Chiniquy, <a name="CPWC" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#CPWC"><cite title="source">The Priest The Woman and The Confessional</cite></a> (n.d.) 1-2</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c09127a" href="c09all.htm#c09127a">VI.C.09:127(a)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
